Got it ðŸ‘ Hereâ€™s a simple algorithm to arrange an array in ascending order (easy to remember, exam-friendly).

Algorithm: Ascending Order Using Array
Step 1: Start
Step 2: Read n (number of elements)
Step 3: Read n elements into array a
Step 4: Repeat i from 0 to n-1
    Repeat j from i+1 to n-1
    If a[i] > a[j]
      Swap a[i] and a[j]
Step 5: Display the array
Step 6: Stop

Explanation (short & clear)
Compare each element with the next elements

If the current element is greater, swap

After all comparisons, the array becomes ascending order

Example
Input: 5
Array: 4 2 5 1 3

Output:
1 2 3 4 5

