Easy C Program: Ascending Order
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int a[10], n, i, j, temp;

    scanf("%d", &n);

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d", &a[i]);

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        for(j = i + 1; j < n; j++)
        {
            if(a[i] > a[j])
            {
                temp = a[i];
                a[i] = a[j];
                a[j] = temp;
            }
        }
    }

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
        printf("%d ", a[i]);

    return 0;
}
Very Simple Explanation
Read numbers

Compare two numbers

If first is bigger â†’ swap

Print sorted array

Example
Input

4
9 3 7 1
Output

1 3 7 9
